</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="20ACB28F5460FFB789E7F8BA57CED41A" authorityName="Geiger" authorityYear="2003" box="[460,694,1836,1859]" class="Gastropoda" family="Depressizonidae" genus="Depressizona" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepetellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="57" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exorum">
<emphasis id="D5D8151E5460FFB789E7F8BA57CED41A" box="[460,694,1836,1859]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="57">Depressizona exorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Easter Island has a much thinner shell, lacks the strong axial lamellae at the periphery and none of the three known specimens have a thickened apertural margin.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
